Wash and dry produce. Quarter @potatoes{12%ounce} (peel if you prefer). Finely chop
@chives{1/4%ounce}. Dice @mini cucumber{1%unit}. Dice @tomato{1%unit}.

In a #microwave-safe bowl{}, season potatoes with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add
@garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} and cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave
until tender and steaming, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry and season with salt and pepper.
Drizzle @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a hot pan; cook chicken until cooked through,
~{5-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and cover with
#foil{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat another drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in same pan. Cook
@cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, and chives, stirring,
until sauce is smooth and slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

In a #bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%ounce}, cucumber, tomato, and
@honey dijon dressing{1.5%ounce}.

Spoon sauce over chicken and potatoes. Serve with salad.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.